review: dont Go to parvathy hospital especially to meet dr Swathi ...******* ** *** *********** we are about to lose my wife and child during pregnancy by gods grace we survived...we were dng regular checkups for 8 months in parvathi hospital..during the checkup she told us everything is fine and there is minor problem that is umbilical artery  resistance of child for that she has given arg 9 sachets ..even what ever my wife was complaining abt problems she was saying its normal...whatever she said we trusted blindly for 8 months...after 8 months my wife got stomach pain and we went for checkup in our home town ...that doctor shouted on us and said that we have to do delivery within 1 hour..after operation my baby born with blue colour as she did not get blood in womb...after 1 month of battle she survived.meanwhile we showed our previous reports to many doctors...in reports its clearly showing that baby is not getting sufficient food or blood from many days due to that blood is clotted in my wife stomach due to umbilical resistance.it was happening for many days even my wife complaining abt stomach pain to dr Swathi many times she was saying  it is minor problem..*** ** ** *** ********* ******* *** ** **** **** *****..even after delivery we showed our previous reports to 2-3 gynics everyone is saying umbilical resistance is major problem and we need to take extra care and the medication... ** * **** ****** **** ** ********** **** ** ** ** ************ ****** **** ** ***we know the pain when my new born baby is in hospital for 1 month...so i dont want others to suffer like me..choice is yours...

review: After reading the reviews of dr.swathi i wanted to continue my pregnancy journey with her. In my experience the doctor is very good. I had normal delivery. The pain started around 10.00 pm at night. I delivered the baby at 3:31 am. She immediately came and saw me and delevered my baby.She is very confident and well experienced. She made sure i was alright after giving birth.She encouraged me for normal delivery. The staff in parvathi hospital are not at all friendly and they did not guid me properly. The only best thing in parvathi hospital is dr.swathi apsani.
